250 g Chorizo Sausage, uncased
6 unit(s) Flour Tortillas
56 g Spring Mix
56 g Onion, sliced
1 unit(s) Tomato
1 tbsp Mexican Seasoning
2 tbsp Tomato Sauce Base
½ cup Cheddar Cheese, shredded
2 tbsp Ranch Dressing
1 unit(s) Beef Broth Concentrate
0.06 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Sugar*
½ tbsp Oil*
0.06 tsp Pepper*

Heat a large non-stick pan over high heat.
When the pan is hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, chorizo, onions, and Mexican seasoning.
Cook, breaking up chorizo into smaller pieces, until no pink remains, 4-5 min.**
Reduce heat to medium.
Add tomato sauce base, beef broth concentrate, 1/8 tsp (1/4 tsp) sugar and 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) water. ﻿
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Stir to mix then, r emove from heat.

Wrap tortillas in paper towels.
Microwave until tortillas are warm and flexible, 1 min. (TIP: You can skip this step if you don't want to warm tortillas!)

Cut tomato into 1/2-inch pieces.
Add spring mix, tomatoes and ranch dressing to a large bowl. Toss to coat.

Arrange tortillas on a clean surface.
Top each tortilla with some of the salad mix.
Divide chorizo mixture over top.
Sprinkle cheese over top and divide wraps between plates.
Serve any remaining salad alongside.

If you've opted to get chorizo, cook and plate it in the same way the recipe instructs you to cook and plate the beef.**